start.label: judge not that you be not judged
people who live in glass houses shouldn't throw stones

related_ngsl.related_word_forms: criticise, criticised, criticises, criticising, criticized, criticizes, criticizing

examples.en: He has no occasion to criticize me.
The paper criticized the new movie
It's not your place to criticize me!
It is not her place to criticize me!
It is always easier to criticize than to compose.
Which of you am I to criticize?
He has been criticized for incompetence.
She can't handle it when people criticize her.
She didn't want to be heard to criticize him.
His boss criticized him for his sloppy work habits.
With the benefit of hindsight, it's easy to criticize.
Ron does nothing but criticize and complain all the time.
The new law has been widely criticized.
The editor criticized the author's work as trite.
The decision has been strongly criticized by teachers.
The report has been criticized as inaccurate and incomplete.
You refuse to help and then criticize me for not doing it right? You're impossible!
